 ll[AtlasTeal] (-3,0) circle (3pt);
tikzpicture
center
The closed circle at $-3$ indicates that $-3$ is included.

Treat this as a three-part inequality, performing the same operation 
on all parts:

Subtract 4 from all parts:
\[
 -2 - 4 < 3x + 4 - 4 \leq 13 - 4
\]
\[
 -6 < 3x \leq 9
\]

Divide all parts by 3:
\[
 -2 < x \leq 3
\]

**Solution:** $(-2, 3]$

