center

Solve each inequality separately:

**First inequality:** $x + 3 < 1 \Rightarrow x < -2$

**Second inequality:** $x - 2 > 4 \Rightarrow x > 6$

The solution is the **union**: $x < -2$ or $x > 6$.

**Interval notation:** $(-\infty, -2) \cup (6, \infty)$

